<p>I think I may have c# inheritance issue.</p>  <p>When ran, the code below produces a, "An exception of type 'System.NullReferenceException' occurred" error message.</p>  <p>When debugging in Visual Studio, I see that the variable "path" is always null in my "Finder" class.</p>  <p>It doesn't seem to be even getting to the "GetUrl" method in the the "WebConnector" class, which probably explains the null error message I get, but I'm not sure why it's not able to get to that method in the first place.</p>  <p>Am I inheriting the base class wrong?</p>  <p>Thanks!</p>  <p>WebConnector.cs:</p>  <pre><code>public class WebConnector {     public String GetUrl(string Id, String baseUrl)     {         string right = String.Format("/a('{0}')/b", Id);         return baseUrl + right;      } </code></pre>  <p>baseClass.cs:</p>  <pre><code>public class BaseClass {      public WebConnector Connector { get; set; }  } </code></pre>  <p>Finder.cs:</p>  <pre><code>public class Finder : BaseClass {      public String GetBuild()     {         var path = Connector.GetUrl(Id, baseUrl);  //always null??     }  } </code></pre>